#load noise and clean Live dataset
if os.path.exists('model/noise_X.npy'):
    noise_X = np.load('model/noise_X.npy')
    clean_Y = np.load('model/clean_Y.npy')
else:
    for root, dirs, directory in os.walk(path):#loop all images from dataset
        for j in range(len(directory)):
            img = cv2.imread(root+"/"+directory[j])#read clean image
            img = cv2.resize(img, (256, 256))
            name = "noisy_"+directory[j]
            noise = cv2.imread("Dataset/Live/Noisy_folder/"+name)#read noise image
            noise = cv2.resize(noise, (256, 256))
            noise_X.append(noise)#create training array with clean and noise images
            clean_Y.append(img)
    noise_X = np.asarray(noise_X)
    clean_Y = np.asarray(clean_Y)
    np.save('model/noise_X',noise_X)
    np.save('model/clean_Y',clean_Y)
X = np.load('model/X.npy') #load columbia splice images data
Y = np.load('model/Y.npy')    
print("LIVE Dataset Loaded")
print("Total images found in Noise & Clean Dataset = "+str(noise_X.shape[0]))
print("Total images found in Columbia Splice Images Dataset = "+str(X.shape[0]))

In [6]:
#function to calculate MAP between true and splice detected images
def calculate_mean_absolute_precision(true_images, predicted_images):
    num_images = true_images.shape[0]
    precision_scores = []
    for i in range(num_images):
        # Flatten the images to 1D arrays
        true_flat = true_images[i].flatten()
        predicted_flat = predicted_images[i].flatten()
        # Calculate precision for the current image
        precision = precision_score(np.round(true_flat), np.round(predicted_flat))
        precision_scores.append(precision)
    # Calculate the mean of precision scores
    mean_precision = np.mean(precision_scores)
    return mean_precision
In [7]:
noise_clean = load_model("model/noise_detect_clean.keras")
#Defining & Loading various layers of RIFD model
input_img = Input(shape=(256, 256, 3))
#noise detection layer
x = Conv2D(64, (3, 3), activation='relu', padding='same')(input_img)
x = MaxPooling2D((2, 2), padding='same')(x)
# denoise layer
x = Conv2D(32, (3, 3), activation='relu', padding='same')(x)
x = MaxPooling2D((2, 2), padding='same')(x)
#similarity calculation
x = Conv2D(16, (3, 3), activation='relu', padding='same')(x)
similarity = MaxPooling2D((2, 2), padding='same')(x)
x = Conv2D(16, (3, 3), activation='relu', padding='same')(similarity)
x = UpSampling2D((2, 2))(x)
x = Conv2D(32, (3, 3), activation='relu', padding='same')(x)
x = UpSampling2D((2, 2))(x)
x = Conv2D(64, (3, 3), activation='relu', padding='same')(x)
x = UpSampling2D((2, 2))(x)
adnet = Conv2D(3, (3, 3), activation='sigmoid', padding='same')(x)
rifd_model = Model(input_img, adnet)
rifd_model.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='mean_squared_error')
if os.path.exists("model/rifd.keras") == False:
    model_check_point = ModelCheckpoint(filepath='model/rifd.keras', verbose = 1, save_best_only = True)
    hist = rifd_model.fit(X_train, y_train, batch_size = 32, epochs = 50, validation_data=(X_test, y_test), callbacks=[model_check_point], verbose=1)
    f = open('model/rifd.pckl', 'wb')
    pickle.dump(hist.history, f)
    f.close()    
else:
    rifd_model.load_weights("model/rifd.keras")
#performing prediction on test data    
predict = rifd_model.predict(X_test)
#calling MAP function with true and predicted images
map = calculate_mean_absolute_precision(y_test, predict)
print("RIFD-Net MAP Score = "+str(map))

#function to localize splice region from predicted frame
def localizeSplice(frame):
    frame = cv2.cvtColor(frame, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)
    cv2.imwrite("test.png", frame*255)
    frame = cv2.imread("test.png")
    hsv = cv2.cvtColor(frame, cv2.COLOR_BGR2HSV)
    lower = np.array([35, 50, 50])
    upper = np.array([85, 255, 255])
    mask = cv2.inRange (hsv, lower, upper)
    contours,temp = cv2.findContours(mask.copy(), cv2.RETR_TREE, cv2.CHAIN_APPROX_SIMPLE)
    max = 0
    index = 0
    for i in range(len(contours)):
      if len(contours[i]) > max:
          max = len(contours[i])
          index = i
    green_area = contours[index] 
    x, y, w, h = cv2.boundingRect(green_area)
    return x, y, w, h

#function to redd input image and then denoise and predict splice region
def detectSplice(image_path):
    image = cv2.imread(image_path)
    image = cv2.resize(image, (256, 256))
    temp = []
    temp.append(image)
    test = np.asarray(temp)
    test = test.astype('float32')
    test = test/255
    denoise = noise_clean.predict(test)#clean the noise image
    denoise = denoise[0]
    denoise = cv2.resize(denoise, (256, 256))
    denoise = cv2.fastNlMeansDenoisingColored(image,None,20,20,7,21)
    temp = []
    temp.append(denoise)
    test = np.asarray(temp)
    test = test.astype('float32')
    test = test/255
    predict = rifd_model.predict(test)#predict splice image
    predict = predict[0]
    super_image = cv2.detailEnhance(denoise, sigma_s=10, sigma_r=0.15) #applying cv2 super resolution algorithm on image to further clear detection
    x, y, w, h = localizeSplice(predict)
    cv2.rectangle(denoise,(x, y),(x+w, y+h),(0, 0, 255), 2)
    cv2.rectangle(super_image,(x, y),(x+w, y+h),(0, 0, 255), 2)
    image = cv2.cvtColor(image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)
    denoise = cv2.cvtColor(denoise, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)
    predict = cv2.cvtColor(predict, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)
    super_image = cv2.cvtColor(super_image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)
    f, axarr = plt.subplots(1,4, figsize=(12,4)) 
    axarr[0].imshow(image)
    axarr[0].title.set_text('Noisy Original Image')
    axarr[1].imshow(denoise)
    axarr[1].title.set_text('Denoise Image')
    axarr[2].imshow(predict)
    axarr[2].title.set_text('Forgery Detected Image')
    axarr[3].imshow(super_image)
    axarr[3].title.set_text('Super Enhance Image')
    plt.show()
